abstract.gco:CharacterString: This point shapefile represents cities and towns in the United States at 1:2,000,000 scale. This layer is part of the 2014 ESRI Data and Maps collection for ArcGIS 10.2.

purpose.gco:CharacterString: U.S. National Atlas Cities provides information about the locations, names, and populations of cities and towns for conducting geographic analysis on national and large regional scales.

credit.gco:CharacterString: National Atlas of the United States, ESRI and U.S. Geological Survey. (2014). United States National Atlas Cities, 1972-2004. ESRI.

measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: The shapefile is converted to file geodatabase (FGDB) format using tools in ArcGIS. The geometry is checked, and if needed repaired.
After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
The geospatial part of this data set was originally extracted from the USGS 1:2,000,000-scale Digital Line Graphs (DLG) - Manmade Features. The horizontal positional accuracy is about 2 kilometers.

description.gco:CharacterString: Updates 1990 and 1998 population figures for Newtown, Connecticut were updated. County and county FIPS fields for the town of Bloomfield, CO were updated and it was listed as the county seat for Bloomfield County. County seats were added for counties where they were missing. Please note that Shannon County, SD; Todd County, SD; Kings, NY; Bronx, NY; Queens, NY; and Richmond, NY do not have official county seats. Incorporated place names were compared with those from the 2004 GNIS database. GNIS names were used where there were discrepancies. New incorporated places were added; duplicate points and places no longer incorporated were removed. Positions of all incorporated places were adjusted to match GNIS coordinates. Minor positional corrections of incorporated places were made using 1999 Hydrography Features of the United States and 1999 County Boundaries of the United States as references. The population range values were adjusted to reflect 2000 population figures and the POP_2000 attribute was added; earlier population figures were dropped.

The following steps were performed by Esri: Downloaded the compressed file from the National Atlas of the United States® and extracted it. Removed unneeded attributes. Added the STATUS attribute and populated it with the text removed from the FEATURE attribute for all records where FEATURE was not "Populated Place". For the records where FEATURE was "Populated Place", attribute STATUS remains blank. Removed attribute FEATURE. Renamed attributes FIPS55 to PLACE_FIPS, STATE to ST_ABBREV, and POP_RANGE to FEATURE. Renamed values of the new FEATURE attribute from "Undetermined" or "0 - 9,999" to "less than 10,000". Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.
The following steps were performed by Esri: For records where POP_2000 has values of -99999 changed the values of FEATURE from "less than 10,000" to "no data".

The following steps were performed by Esri: Added the POP2007 attribute and populated it with values from Esri Data. Converted the data set to SDC. Created projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.
Converted the dataset into a file geodatabase.
